---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Uganda Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/uganda/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kenya for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kenya' },
  { title: 'Rwanda for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/rwanda' },
  { title: 'Tanzania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/tanzania' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'ugandaFit', header: 'Uganda Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UGX$1.85M-2.64M/mo', ugandaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UGX$2.16M-3.09M/mo', ugandaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UGX$1.66M-2.38M/mo', ugandaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UGX$1.55M-2.21M/mo', ugandaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (AAR, Jubilee)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'UGX$300K-800K/mo', ugandaFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'UGX$1.66M-2.64M', annual: 'UGX$19.9M-31.7M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'UGX$2.28M-3.52M', annual: 'UGX$27.3M-42.2M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'UGX$3.06M-4.72M', annual: 'UGX$36.7M-56.7M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'UGX$100K-300K/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'UGX$500K-1.5M/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Uganda 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Uganda. Gorilla trekking, English-speaking, pleasant climate, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Uganda"
  subheadline="Uganda offers mountain gorilla trekking, English as official language, pleasant highland climate, and 'Pearl of Africa' beauty—an authentic East African adventure with primate experiences."
  heroImage="/images/countries/uganda-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Uganda</h2>
  <p>
    Uganda offers mountain gorilla trekking (half Rwanda's cost), English as official language, pleasant highland climate, and diverse wildlife. For adventurous retirees seeking authentic African experience with primate encounters, Uganda provides exceptional value and natural beauty.
  </p>

  <p>
    Kampala is the capital with best healthcare. Entebbe offers lakeside living near airport. Bwindi provides gorilla access. Jinja has Nile adventures. Most expats choose Kampala/Entebbe for healthcare; explore regions for experiences.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Nairobi backup common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English and Swahili (official)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> UGX$3M-6M/month (~$800-1,600 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Highland tropical; pleasant year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Friendly; diverse; wildlife-rich</li>
      <li><strong>Nairobi access:</strong> 1-hour flight for complex care</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Uganda Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Uganda healthcare is limited—IHK (International Hospital Kampala) and private clinics provide reasonable care. Many doctors trained internationally. Public system underfunded. Complex cases typically evacuate to Nairobi (1-hour flight). International insurance with evacuation essential.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare in Kampala improving. Expat community growing. Kenya provides essential backup for serious conditions. Regional healthcare cooperation through East African Community.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Nairobi Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Kenya provides essential medical backup—Nairobi is 1-hour flight with excellent hospitals. Include Kenya in insurance coverage. Kampala handles routine care; Nairobi provides specialist backup. Remote areas require evacuation capability.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Uganda has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-90 days via e-visa. Simple application. Single and multiple entry options.
  </p>

  <h3>East African Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    90-day multi-country visa for Uganda, Kenya, Rwanda. Good for regional exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Special Pass</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories. Renewable.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For permanent settlement. Various categories. Apply through immigration.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Uganda:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Yellow fever vaccination required; insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Nairobi coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Uganda</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Kenya evacuation coverage essential. Kampala private care handles routine needs. Nairobi provides specialist backup. Regional East African coverage ideal. Don't economize on coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Uganda, Kenya evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Uganda</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong East Africa network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Nairobi access:</strong> Regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>East African coverage:</strong> Regional mobility</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with East Africa network.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Uganda (UGX ~3,700 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Kampala base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Nairobi network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> East Africa focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Gorilla Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Special pass. Entebbe base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with East Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~UGX$2M/month (~$540). Wildlife focus; Nairobi backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: NGO Retiree, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month pension. Residence permit. Kampala.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~UGX$2.5M/month (~$675). Development community; global backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: East African Explorer, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month income. Tourist visa rotation. Mobile lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with regional mobility.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~UGX$1.7M/month (~$460). Multi-country; flexible.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Uganda safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—Kampala and tourist areas secure. Avoid border regions (DRC, South Sudan). Political situation requires monitoring but expat community thrives. Normal urban precautions apply. Wildlife areas professionally managed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English sufficient?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—English is official language. Business, government, healthcare all in English. Swahili growing but English dominant. British colonial heritage. No language barrier for English speakers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Uganda or Rwanda for gorillas?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Both excellent—Uganda costs half ($800 vs $1,500 permit). Rwanda more developed infrastructure. Uganda has more gorilla families and chimpanzees. Both offer incredible experiences. Uganda better value; Rwanda more polished.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the climate like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Pleasant—highland tropical climate. Kampala (1,200m) has comfortable year-round temperatures. Cooler in mountains. Two rainy seasons but generally manageable. Not the oppressive heat of lowland tropics.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Uganda coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Uganda authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
